>Description:
When setting the preferences for font one has to use a bad, non-standard interface to select the font. There is a standard font dialog that is much better. Use it instead.
>How-To-Repeat:
0: Open DrScheme on a Mac
1: Select the DrScheme -> Preferences... menu item
2: Make sure that the Font tab is selected
3: Look at the GUI-badness and contemplate how much better the standard font selector is
>Fix:
